The paper proposes a framework for collaborative compressive sensing (CCS) and provides an approach to designing optimal CCS systems. The paper also includes experiments with real images to show the effectiveness of the proposed CCS system. Based on this, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory) as the paper deals with the design and optimization of compressive sensing systems. The paper also involves image processing, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.MM (Multimedia). The use of optimization techniques and algorithms suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.SI (Signal Processing).
